block.comment: We have four modes in the project to help you learn the basic music theory and how to play songs in just a few seconds! Press the button on the main menu to start! Group: Practice Mode: virtual keyboard allows you to play any song you want like a real piano. You can also record your music! Game Mode, fast finger and ear training by playing in a Guitar Hero style! Ryan Benkeser: Counting Mode: the rythm in music. Yinxue Bian: Tutorial Mode, learn different kinds of scales and tips to play them!

block.l: In music, there are different note lengths. There are whole notes, half notes, quarter notes, eighth notes, sixteenth notes, and 32nd notes.
For our purposes today, I will teach you how to count between eighth, quarter, half, and whole notes.
Would you like to begin? Say "y" if you are ready. If not, we will start from the beginning. Press 0 if you are bored.
Now try and copy this beat!
Nope, let's try that one again.
Notice how whole notes play for twice as long as half notes. Additionally half notes play for twice as long as quarter notes.
YOU ARE CHEATING! GET OFF THE STAGE!
You will have to start over on your own accord now.
YOU STINK! GET OFF THE STAGE!!!
You will have to start over on your own accord now.
Now you try and copy these two whole notes by pressing the appropriate key when the pink block drops!

You have reached the end of the counting tutorial! If you can answer the following question correctly, you will get your certification in counting!
Which note is equivalent in length to four eighth notes? Say "w" for whole note, "h" for half note, "q" for quarter note or "e" for eighth note.
